mlvpn (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add mlvpn-tui: a terminal monitoring view showing live per-link
    state, peer address, and both sides' RTT/jitter/loss/throughput.
  * Add mlvpnd's local control socket (/run/mlvpn/<tunnel>.sock,
    [control] in config) that mlvpn-tui and other tools read from.
  * Add PacketType::StatsShare so peers exchange their self-reported
    link stats over the authenticated tunnel session.
  * Restructure the crate into a library plus two binaries (mlvpnd,
    mlvpn-tui) so they can share the control-socket JSON schema.
  * Fix systemd unit ExecStart path (/usr/local/bin -> /usr/bin) to
    match where this package actually installs mlvpnd; add
    RuntimeDirectory=mlvpn so the control socket has a writable,
    correctly-owned directory under ProtectSystem=strict.
  * Fix a redundant double session-lock in the Probe reply path, and
    split the per-link receive/probe task into two independent tasks
    to remove a probe-starvation risk under sustained receive load.
  * Add an advisory warning when tunnel.mtu plus protocol overhead is
    likely to exceed a typical 1500-byte physical link MTU.
  * Add GitHub Actions CI (build + unit tests on every push/PR) and a
    release workflow that builds and publishes this .deb on version
    tags.
  * security: fix unauthenticated remote DoS where a single forged
    handshake reply could crash the client daemon (bypassed the
    handshake retry loop via `?`, no source-address check).
  * security: fix replay window being updated before AEAD
    authentication succeeded, letting an unauthenticated attacker
    pre-burn sequence numbers and cause legitimate packets to be
    misclassified as replays and dropped.
  * security: fail closed (instead of silently skipping) the peer
    identity pin check on an unexpected missing remote static key.
  * security: close a permission race on the monitoring control
    socket by tightening the process umask around its creation
    instead of chmod-ing it after the fact.
  * security: rate-limit pre-session handshake attempts to blunt a
    CPU-exhaustion flood from unauthenticated senders.
  * Remove debian/compat: it conflicted with the debhelper-compat (= 13)
    Build-Depends and made every build fail with "debhelper compat
    level specified both in debian/compat and via build-dependency on
    debhelper-compat".
  * Build and publish arm64 .deb packages alongside amd64 (native
    ubuntu-24.04-arm GitHub Actions runner; no cross-compilation
    needed since Architecture: any already covers this).
  * Fix README setup instructions: wrong genkey/mkdir ordering and a
    missing mlvpn system user/group creation step meant following them
    as written would fail; rewrote with a full install/config/verify
    walkthrough for the .deb + systemd path.
  * Add mlvpnd firewall-setup: detects firewalld/ufw/nftables/iptables
    and opens the UDP ports a config's [[links]] need, with --dry-run
    and --remove. Ships in this package automatically (same binary).
  * CI: replace release-deb.yml with release.yml, which builds this
    .deb alongside a new RPM (packaging/rpm/mlvpn.spec, for current
    Fedora and RHEL/Rocky/Alma) and publishes both to one Release.
  * Relicense from MIT to AGPL-3.0-only.

